[[Image:Hhof maurice richard.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Maurice Richard Trophy on display at the [[Hockey Hall of Fame]]]]
The '''Maurice 'Rocket' Richard [[Trophy]]''' is awarded annually to the leading goal scorer in the [[National Hockey League]]. It was donated to the [[NHL]] by the [[Montreal Canadiens]] hockey club in [[1998-99 NHL season|1998-99]].

==History==
[[Image:Richard And Trophy.jpg|left|thumb|The Rocket poses with the Trophy named after him]]
The Maurice 'Rocket' Richard Trophy is named in honour of [[Montreal Canadiens]] [[Winger (ice hockey)|right winger]] [[Maurice Richard|Maurice "Rocket" Richard]]. Richard led the NHL in goal scoring five times during his career. In [[1944-45 NHL season|1944-45]] he became the first player in NHL history to score [[50 goals in 50 games|50 goals]] in one season.

In the history of the NHL, counting co-leaders as fractional wins, [[Montreal Canadiens]] have led the league in goal-scoring 14 times, [[Toronto Maple Leafs]] 11 times, [[Boston Bruins]], [[Detroit Red Wings]], and [[Chicago Blackhawks]] 8.5 times each, and [[Edmonton Oilers]] 6 times.
{{clear}}

